kages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/preview.ts` exists but is empty. Plan says to populate it with a `global.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__` assignment importing from `'../../../documentation.json'`.\n4. `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.json` has `emitDecoratorMetadata: true` but no `resolveJsonModule`. Plan says add `\"resolveJsonModule\": true`.\n5. `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.doc.json` does NOT exist. Plan says create it extending `./tsconfig.json` with `include: [\"../src/**/*.ts\"]` and `exclude: [\"../**/*.spec.ts\", \"../**/*.stories.ts\"]`.\n6. `main.ts` has no `addons` or `docs` config -- empty `addons: []`.\n\n## Relevant File Contents\n\n`packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/main.ts`:\n```typescript\nimport type { StorybookConfig } from '@storybook/angular';\n\nconst config: StorybookConfig = {\n  stories: ['../**/*.@(mdx|stories.@(js|jsx|ts|tsx))'],\n  addons: [],\n  framework: {\n    name: '@storybook/angular',\n    options: {},\n  },\n};\n\nexport default config;\n```\n\n`packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.json`:\n```json\n{\n  \"extends\": \"../tsconfig.json\",\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"emitDecoratorMetadata\": true\n  },\n  \"exclude\": [\"../**/*.spec.ts\"],\n  \"include\": [\n    \"../src/**/*.stories.ts\",\n    \"../src/**/*.stories.js\",\n    \"../src/**/*.stories.jsx\",\n    \"../src/**/*.stories.tsx\",\n    \"../src/**/*.stories.mdx\",\n    \"*.js\",\n    \"*.ts\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n`packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json` (storybook/build-storybook targets):\n```json\n\"storybook\": {\n  \"continuous\": true,\n  \"executor\": \"@storybook/angular:start-storybook\",\n  \"options\": {\n    \"port\": 4200,\n    \"configDir\": \"packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook\",\n    \"browserTarget\": \"ngx-smart-components:build-storybook\",\n    \"compodoc\": false\n  }\n},\n\"build-storybook\": {\n  \"executor\": \"@storybook/angular:build-storybook\",\n  \"outputs\": [\"{options.outputDir}\"],\n  \"options\": {\n    \"outputDir\": \"dist/storybook/ngx-smart-components\",\n    \"configDir\": \"packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook\",\n    \"browserTarget\": \"ngx-smart-components:build-storybook\",\n    \"compodoc\": false\n  }\n}\n```\n\n`root package.json` devDependencies (abbreviated):\n- `@storybook/angular`: `10.3.5`\n- `storybook`: `10.3.5`\n- `@nx/storybook`: `^22.6.5`\n- No `@compodoc/compodoc` entry\n\n## Pre-Verified Package Behavior Claims\n\n<pre_verified source=\"npm list output\" claim_id=\"pv-1\">\n  <claim>`@compodoc/compodoc` 1.2.1 is installed transitively (marked extraneous) and will be available at build time even before it is pinned as a direct devDependency.</claim>\n  <evidence method=\"Bash\">\n    @ngx-smart-components/source@0.0.0 D:\\projects\\github\\LayZeeDK\\ngx-smart-components\n    └── @compodoc/compodoc@1.2.1 extraneous\n  </evidence>\n</pre_verified>\n\n## Question\n\nThe plan's step 4 populates `preview.ts` with `import docJson from '../../../documentation.json'`. At the time TypeScript compiles `preview.ts`, `documentation.json` does not yet exist (it is generated by compodoc which runs first in the Nx executor chain). Should the plan proceed as written -- trusting that compodoc runs before the Storybook compile step -- or is there a safer pattern for the JSON import that avoids a hard compile-time dependency on a generated file?","agentId":"a4f7f970fa9fe5bdd","agentType":"lz-advisor:advisor","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Proceed as written -- the `@storybook/angular` executor runs compodoc before the TS compile step, so `documentation.json` exists when `preview.ts` is type-checked.\n2. Add `documentation.json` to the package's `.gitignore` to prevent committing the generated artifact.\n3. For first-run safety on fresh clones, seed an empty `packages/ngx-smart-components/documentation.json` containing `{}` and commit it, OR use `import type`-free dynamic shape: declare `const docJson: unknown` via a 