he executor writes it beside `project.json`, the import breaks silently.\n2. Verify the `.gitignore` entry is anchored (`/documentation.json`) so it only ignores the root artifact, not any future nested file of the same name.\n3. Assuming `tsconfig.doc.json` is actually consumed by the compodoc executor (unverified), do pass `-p .storybook/tsconfig.doc.json` via `compodocArgs` in `project.json`. Verify the executor's default `-p` resolution before acting -- the `@storybook/angular` builder defaults to the project's `tsconfig.json`, so the new file may be dead config.\n4. Run `npx nx build-storybook ngx-smart-components` and grep the output HTML for a populated \"Compodoc\" tab on one component to confirm the JSON actually hydrates at runtime.\n\n**Critical:** The `docJson` import has no runtime guard -- if compodoc generation is ever skipped or fails silently, Storybook boot throws a module-not-found. Consider a try/catch or dynamic import with fallback to keep Storybook bootable when docs are stale."}],"totalDurationMs":9761,"totalTokens":17832,"totalToolUseCount":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11451,"cache_read_input_tokens":5927,"output_tokens":448,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":11451},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
